@page "/faq"

<PageTitle>FAQ</PageTitle>

<div class="card mb-4">
    <div class="card-body">
        <h1 class="card-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="card mb-3">
    <div class="card-body">
        <h5 class="card-title">How much are HOA dues?</h5>
        <p class="mb-0">Annual dues are <strong>$500 per household</strong>. Dues cover shared community services, primarily trash collection, as well as maintenance of the neighborhood entrances and other common expenses.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="card mb-3">
    <div class="card-body">
        <h5 class="card-title">When are dues collected?</h5>
        <p>Dues are collected each year from <strong>March 1st through March 31st</strong>.</p>
        <p class="mb-0">Payment must be received by March 31st to avoid penalties.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="card mb-3">
    <div class="card-body">
        <h5 class="card-title">What happens if I don't pay my dues on time?</h5>
        <p>A <strong>10% late fee</strong> will be added to your account each month that dues remain unpaid past the March 31st deadline.</p>
        <p>If dues remain unpaid for an extended period, trash service to your household may be suspended.</p>
        <p class="mb-0">In extreme cases, a lien may be placed on your property to recover the outstanding balance.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="card mb-3">
    <div class="card-body">
        <h5 class="card-title">Who provides trash service?</h5>
        <p>Trash collection is provided by <strong>GFL Environmental</strong> as part of your HOA dues.</p>
        <p class="mb-0">If you have any issues with pickup or need to schedule a special collection, contact GFL customer service at <a href="tel:816-380-5595"><strong>816-380-5595</strong></a>.</p>
    </div>
</div>
